===Verb===
{{en-verb|abnegat}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[deny]] (oneself something); to [[renounce]] or give up (a right, a power, a [[claim]], a privilege, a convenience). {{defdate|First attested in the early 17<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>
#* {{quote-news|date=December 10 1898|title=Asbell v. State|work=The Pacific Reporter|volume=55|page=339|passage=To compel a state, upon theories of doubtful statutory interpretation, to appear as defendant suitor in its own courts, and to litigate with private parties as to whether it had '''abnegated''' its sovereignty of exemption, would be intolerable.}}
#* {{quote-journal|date=1875 January|journal=Brownson's Quarterly Review|page=20|passage=All ancient and modern histories of nations '''abnegate''' God.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[relinquish]]; to [[surrender]]; to [[abjure]]. {{defdate|First attested in the mid 18<sup>th</sup> century.}}<ref name=SOED/>

